data.title: Top 40 Wedding Bands & DJs in Tennessee
data.meta_description: Find your perfect wedding musicians in Tennessee at Zola. We'll help you narrow down your musician search in minutes.
data.text:
Heres the deal: You want a luxury wedding day in Nashville, TN. Congratulations youve found the right place. At Turn Up Nashville, were passionate about providing a stress-free experience, that creates memories that last a lifetime. We bring a whole new meaning to event entertainment by making it relevant, engaging, & all together excellent.

We started in the performance industry as professional dancers and have a passion for being a part of epic celebrations! We love being such an integral part of these special moments and are passionate about every aspect of our performances. From planning and preparation to squeaky clean setups and expert mixing, you and your crowd are the only missing piece to an unforgettable celebration!

We are a group of distinguished artists and professionals with decades of industry experience. We have worked alongside of major artists, performed on national tours, and been featured on shows such as American Idol, The Voice, and The Four. Our band leader, Brennan also has 10+ years of professional event planning experience and has personally performed and/coordinated music for over 400 weddings.

Hey, I'm Justin and I put this company together because of my many, many years in the music business, as well as my vast array of top notch musicians and singers who play and perform with some of the world's top touring acts! I've been playing and touring professionally for almost 15 years now and have toured with artists such as Keith Urban, Kelly Clarkson, Nick Jonas, Selena Gomez, Kane Brown, Shawn Mendes and many more! I know what it takes to put on a great event as well as know what my clients need. I ran a wedding company in Toronto for 5 years before relocating to Nashville so I'm very educated in this space. Lets talk Im flexible.

We are a small group of DJ's in the South East. We love weddings and dancing (and high-end audio equipment). Our distinctive style combines rich musical knowledge spanning genres and decades with a keen social/cultural sensibility. We're there to celebrate with you, infusing energy and joy into the evening by discerning your vibe and enhancing it with tasteful song choices. With equipment and procedures, our vibe is professional. With planning and partying, our vibe is personal. It is this ability to combine excellence with liveliness that is exemplary.

DJ ROCK STEADY is a wedding entertainment service operating out of Murfreesboro, Tennessee. Established in 2016, this business is celebrated for providing events of all kinds with unforgettable music and exciting ambiances. The soundtrack to your special day will feature all of your favorite hits and tunes that are guaranteed to keep your guests on the floor all night. Personable and polished, DJ Rock Steady is fully prepared to keep the party going until the lights come on.

We love what we do. We love all our couples and we love where we live & that so many choose this area to get married in. We feel that love is love, no matter who is getting married, & everyone deserves to have the biggest, best wedding day ever! And we love to share that with each of our couples on so many different levels. Whether we are DJing, officiating, coordinating or any combo of those, we always leave our events feeling like weve added new family to ours!

Introducing DJ Shine, a veteran wedding DJ with five years of expertise in crafting magical moments on the dance floor. DJ Shine's dedication to music transcends boundaries, seamlessly weaving diverse genres to keep your wedding party alive. Renowned for his amiable and cooperative nature, DJ Shine guarantees a hassle-free and enjoyable journey, making him the perfect choice to orchestrate the soundtrack for your wedding celebration.

My passion as a DJ in my business stems from my love for music, creative expression through mixing and sets, connecting with audiences, continuous learning and improvement in my craft, and the entrepreneurial challenge of building a successful enterprise. These factors combine to fuel my enthusiasm and fulfillment in my DJ career. I love DJing weddings because it allows me to celebrate love and happiness, create memorable experiences through music, connect personally with couples and guests, adapt creatively to each unique event, grow professionally, and receive heartfelt appreciation for enhancing such special occasions.

Ive been playing music and entertaining for 20 years. Music has always made me happy ever since I was a little girl. I love doing things that are different and stand out from others. Whether you are getting married or have a special event, I would love to be considered as your DJ. I can provide sound for both your ceremony and reception if needed. For couples getting married, I will include a wedding playlist template for you to pick the songs/genres you would prefer me to play and it will help provide some structure from the start of your ceremony til the end of your reception. I will travel for a fee. Im available weekends and weekdays.

DJ Aries Productions & staff are made up of the most experienced professional DJs. Our goal is, to give excellent customer service and provide the very best DJs. We emphasize quality & professionalism to ensure that all your guests have an enjoyable experience. We Cater to all types of Events, Genres, & Ages of Music, We offer distinct specialties such as Wedding Receptions & Ceremonies, Corporate Events, Quinceaneras, Birthday Parties,.School proms, College Dances, Family Celebrations, Bar & Bat Mitzvahs, interactive Kid Parties, music Video Parties, Bar/Club, Karaoke, Private Events & much, much more.

Groove Factor now offers 3 options for your event, Groove Factor Live, Party Beat, and A'akeela & the Beats! They are all fun and exciting bands that keeps our audiences wanting more after every event! More of what you may ask? More singing, dancing, interaction!!!! Our party style show is fun for all ages and keeps the dance floor packed all night long. We play every genre of songs from the era of Motown all the way to todays hits! Groove Factor is based in Memphis Tn. but our bands travel for weddings, corporate events, casinos, university parties, and nightclubs. We can do it all, because we like to PARTY PARTY PARTY.....ALL NIGHT LONG!!!!

Hey Y'all! I'm Scenic Logan (scenic_logan), founder of Scenic Event Solutions! I have a degree in Audio Production and have performed professionally at weddings for over 10 years! Scenic Event Solutions has 3 DJs on staff and offers various sound and entertainment services including a 360 Video Booth, Wireless Ceremony Sound Systems, Karaoke services, and Audio Guestbooks! But enough about us, we wanna know about you and your big day!

Welcome to Manor Productions, where we specialize in creating unforgettable entertainment experiences. Specializing in weddings and events, we are passionate about delivering exceptional music and ambiance. Our talented DJs curate personalized playlists, ensuring the perfect soundtrack for your special day. With top-notch equipment and a knack for reading the crowd, we keep the dance floor buzzing. We pride ourselves on professionalism, attention to detail, and customer satisfaction. From the initial consultation to flawless execution, Manor Productions goes above and beyond to make your event stress-free and memorable.

Our mission is to create remarkable & impactful experiences for our clients and their guests to remember for a lifetime! We are the place to find dependable, reliable, and quality entertainment services. We are a community of creatives who serve our world as positive examples, role models, and proof that we can improve the lifestyle of our families using our GOD given talents and doing the things we love to do through smart work, dedication, perseverance, and commitment!

I am a Navy Veteran with a passion for music and bringing people together for live events. With over 20 years of experience as a sound engineer and DJ, I will keep the night lively! I look forward to the opportunity to provide you with the best service possible.

Celebrating a wedding? Throwing an epic birthday party or reunion? Any event idea you have, we want to help! Here at Onyx Entertainment in Nashville, our sole mission is to be exactly what you are looking for to make your event special and memorable. We achieve this by providing professionalism, attention-to-detail, and of course, LOTS of fun. Our photo booth, yard games, and lighting rentals will take your event to the next level. Your vision for the event is what we rally around to support you the best we possibly can. Its all about you!

We are Nashville Party Authority - Middle Tennessee's absolute finest in Mobile Disc Jockey and Karaoke Entertainment for weddings and parties. Yes, we agree, it's a lofty claim but we have the goods to back it up. We are happy to make your acquaintance and would be honored to make your next party happen; whether it's an elegant skyline Wedding Reception, Fraternity throw-down, Sweet Sixteen birthday, Bar/Bat Mitzvah, Corporate Event or any special occasion that demands the blending of atmosphere and interaction, optimum lighting, superior audio and, above all, the right mix of music that makes you wanna dance.

A soulful take on the songs you love, from classics of the 1960's all the way to today's top 40 hits. Allow me to curate your music for an unforgettable show at your next event!  PLEASE READ BEFORE CONTACTING ME my minimum fee is $600 for a solo performance. I'd love to create a custom quote for your special event. Thank you!  I've played solo, with a full band, or anywhere in between and have been performing for over a decade. My repertoire spans from 1960s through the present, ranging from Adele to Otis Redding. (Ask for my song list!)

Inspired in the late 1980s, by local radio DJs in the Memphis area, LaShawn DJ Zoom Lester began deejaying by recording music from the radio and using various mixtapes created by popular deejays to create his own music. After deejaying at several middle and high school events, DJ Zoom officially began his professional career in 2007. Over the years, he continued to perfect his craft, making him one of the most sought after deejays in Memphis and the surrounding areas.

The 12 South Band has quickly become one of the most sought-after Entertainment bands in the Country! The band performs over 100 shows each year and has performed for Marriott, the NFL, the PGA, Atlanta Braves NYE, Hall Winery, Panama City Beach NYE, Scott Hamilton Cares, The American Heart Association, Jackson National, multiple city concerts, and countless other corporate events, fundraisers, and celebrity weddings. The band travels extensively each year having performed in over 25 States and overseas.

Rock Bottom Entertainment is a top of the line wedding DJ / Entertainment company based out of Asheville, North Carolina. With more than 15 years of industry experience, the entertainers here are confident in their ability to help make every celebration unforgettable. They understand that no two weddings are alike and will use their performance to emphasize each couple's unique love story.

At Abe One DJs, we are passionate about providing the perfect musical backdrop for your special events. Whether its a wedding, private party, corporate event, or any other important gathering, our team of enthusiastic DJs will play the music you love and your guests will want to hear. With over four decades of experience, you can rest assured that we have the knowledge and expertise to handle any type of event, big or small. And because we have a team of DJs on hand, you never have to worry about a backup plan. Weve got you covered!

The Nashville Blue Tones- Music City's premier variety dance band! The Nashville Blue Tones have performed in some of the countrys most prestigious venues and with some of the worlds most acclaimed artists such as Shania Twain and the legendary Aretha Franklin. A love for the unique settings of special events and wedding receptions was cultivated and The Nashville Blue Tones found their niche. Today the Nashville Blue Tones combines versatility and experience to create an entertainment experience unlike any other. With an extensive song list, the band plays hits from all genres with the goal of making your special day absolutely amazing!

Terry's DJ services provides the ultimate DJ entertainment for weddings, class reunions, corporate events, school dances, and parties of all sizes. Since I do not have employees, you will receive my personal attention at every function. The client(s) and I will start with a private consultation and discuss the events, the music and the timing. The consultation also gives me a chance to get to know you better and further personalize your event. I can also coordinate with your photographer, videographer, wedding coordinator and any other professional in attendance.

Since 2006, Gracie Hays has played hundreds of weddings all across the United States. Playing music professionally since she was only eleven years old, Gracie has truly grown into her musical career and has developed her own company & brand, Gracie Hays Music. Through Gracie Hays Music, she has provided countless weddings with custom tailored music to fit each couple's unique musical tastes. From Beatles to Bluegrass to Bach, Gracie will be able to meet your unique needs for your special day!

Adam Clark & Derek Hughes created The Nashville Wedding Band in Nashville TN to give their clients an experience of a lifetime. After 25 years of music city experience, performing and working together with some of the biggest names* in Country & Rock, this duo decided to take on a new and exciting journey of establishing a Nashville-based wedding band. With access to some of the best touring musicians and singers in the nation, they were able to compile a band unlike any other to take the wedding experience to the next level.

With 7 years of DJing experience I try to bring a happy medium of the classics and modern hits. Being a smaller operation we can focus on providing the most personal and detailed experience as possible. We try to have you as involved as you would like. Being more as a team then a vendor.

Top Tier is live music at the highest level! Top Tier is a fun, high-energy variety band that has 5 lead vocalists to offer a diverse repertoire that spans over 7 decades and encompasses almost every style of music. The band was formed 14 years ago and consists of top notch, experienced musicians with a passion for performing. They can perform as a 5-piece, 6-piece (with sax), or an 8-piece (with a 3-piece horn section). There are over 200 fantastic reviews of Top Tier that have been posted online. So when you want live music at the highest level, look no further than Top Tier!

Simple. Elegant. Beautiful. If this is what you envision for your wedding, classical guitar may be exactly what you're looking for. Guitarist Rob Higginbotham brings a blend of virtuosic classical guitar repertoire and contemporary fingerstyle guitar to add that special touch to any occasion. He has been featured on NPR, performed with the Nashville Symphony and played over 60 weddings last year. With over 25 years of playing experience, you can be assured of a flawless performance and a treasured memory.

The Beasley Brothers are a Country/Rock music group based in Nashville. From being selected as one of the top North Alabama bands in 2015, to opening for Kansas, they have made their name known throughout the southeast. From the ages of 3 and 4, Jackson and Lawson Beasley spent most of their time with toy guitars singing along to anything ranging from The Beatles and Eagles, to the CMT top 20. Now as The Beasley Brothers, they were listed among the "15 North Alabama Musicians To Watch". The Beasley Brothers perform at a variety of different events ranging from weddings and parties, to large music festivals throughout southeast.

Bueller is the Top 80s cover band booked in Nashville and surrounding areas. The band has performed over 2000+ parties, weddings and corporate events over the last 15 years. Bueller is comprised of professional musicians who've been playing together for several years. Their tightly knit sound, 5 lead vocalists, extensive song list, and ability to tailor and transform their performance to entertain any crowd puts Bueller in a class that is unmatched by any other band. The band can also be booked as a 3 or 4 piece if budget is an issue.

With over 10 years in Mid-South weddings & corporate parties, we understand that no matter what type of celebration you are planning; no matter how large or small; no matter how formal or casual; you should be able to have professional, reliable entertainment that will enhance your event. Our goal is to always provide you with the best DJ, music, karaoke, trivia, and entertainment around. Thank you so much for checking with us and allowing us to bring The Funn!

Whether its making that special day of marriage beyond perfection, creating the quintessential EP and/or mixtape, turning up at that sweet 16 or prom, or even bringing families together in dance... there is only one choice and that is Dj Dutty Laundry. DJ Dutty Laundry holds many titles: Wedding DJ, Entertainer, "Mr. Excitement", host, emcee, photo-booth man, light man, "the chief party rocker" He will do whatever it takes to make your big day a smashing success.

DJ1LUV Entertainment Karaoke & DJ Service: fun and professional entertainment for every occasion in Memphis (Shelby County), North Mississippi (Desoto County) and Eastern Arkansas; package rates to meet every budget, discounts available for non-profit groups. LeVelle is a professional, energetic, and charismatic person who has a genuine love and appreciation for music. He also a family man he uses his passion for the arts to reach many and is handing down the musical legacy to his children. Moreover, LeVelle is a dynamic Emcee and offers an extensive music catalog to tailor any occasion.

A respect of nostalgia with a modern twist, Nathan Belt & The Buckles pay homage to the classic twangy rock n roll you love. Influences of Merle Haggard-era country and Roy Orbison/Elvis Presley style vocals, this bands sound is enjoyed by audiences both musically versed and new. Each have backed legendary artists such as Wanda Jackson, Billy Joe Shaver, Los Straitjackets, Chuck Mead (BR549), Garry Tallent (The E Street Band), Emmylou Harris and Billy Burnette to name a few. If youre fortunate enough to experience their show live, you'll be met with an energetic set, a compelling desire to dance and their signature, sharp dressed style.

Soulful, stylish, energetic, and unique  these are just some of the words used by fans to describe 30Vice. A band consisting of a multi-national lineup of talented musicians, 30Vice combines its cultural influences to create a one-of-a-kind sound with a South Florida flare. 30Vice is not an out for hire group pieced together for events, nor does the band perform using pre-recorded audio tracks (similar to karaoke). Instead, the band you book is the band you get that performs 100% live, high-energy music. And 30Vice has also appeared and performed in the Hollywood feature film, Pitch Perfect 3

Bobby and The Aristocats are a high energy SHOWSTOPPER party and dance band ready to WOW you and your guests. Their welcoming, energetic, and engaging bandleader Bobby along with The Aristocats will have your guests having fun and dancing all night. Their expansive song list ranges from the 50's all the way to today's Top Hits within every genre of music.

Trained at Dubspot School of Electronic Music in New York City, Davis Mallory's DJ style is influenced by his childhood in Atlanta, Georgia, time exploring the music scenes of Chicago, Europe and New York, Los Angeles and Music City: Nashville, Tennessee. Davis has performed at countless weddings, nightclubs and fundraisers with some career highlights including: the Denver Nuggets Halftime Show, opening for Eurovision winner Netta in Stockholm, Country Music Fest 2014, Amsterdam's Club NYX and MadFox, the Anheuser-Busch Awards opening for James Corden and KC & the Sunshine Band, and Vanderbilt Homecoming playing with Aaron Carter.

A lot can change in twenty years, and events are bigger business than ever. Back then in Nashville nobody but Burning Las Vegas was pioneering their BLV brand with a choreographed, high energy multi-vocal front line. Nowadays it almost seems like an industry standard. But here's something that hasn't changed: Burning Las Vegas does it better. Better, because they can list all the celebrity name checks and society calendar landmarks if its what you need, but they know that right now, if youre reading this, its really only your event that matters.

Providing the music for someones special day is something I take very seriously. I consider it an honor to have been chosen to provide the service for such an important day. Not to mention my love for music and people for me the two just kind of go hand-in-hand.

We know every bride is different and that their celebration has to be unique! We love the love (I know it sounds cheesy) it reminds us of why we got married, and we feel uplifted every single time. We connect with our couples and strive to be the best wedding DJs and emcee you can find the Smoky Mountains. Its why we offer an app that helps couples choose their main song selections. They can share the app with friends and family to add more of their favorite dance songs. Unlike a lot of DJs out there, we dont require the internet to play songs. We own all of our music; nothing needs to load or buffer, we can bring the party anywhere!

All of our DJs at Entertain! are professionally trained with years of experience and hundreds of events under their belt. Our DJs can beat match and mix music seamlessly to create a one-of-a-kind experience that will keep your guests dancing all night. Don't settle for a DJ with outdated skills who only plays music from a laptop and just fades in/out. You want a DJ who can read your crowd and anticipate what your guests want to hear. Entertain! DJs provides all of those skills, plus the ability to MC your event. We make it easy for you to enjoy your event so you can be stress free and focus on having a fun time!

Born and raised in Florence, Alabama, Anne Landis Jetton began classical training at the age of five and studied violin at Vanderbilt Universitys Blair School of Music. She is a founding member of Jet Set Strings, a professional string quartet and trio based in Nashville, Tennessee, and maintains a regular schedule as an instructor and freelance violinist. As both a soloist and ensemble member, Anne Landis performs at weddings and special events in the Nashville, Tennessee and Florence, Alabama areas. She resides in Nashville with her husband, Jeff Jetton, accordion player and frequent musical collaborator.

Every DJ company in the Knoxville area seems to advertise themselves as experts and professionals  only Pro-Audio (who has been in business since 1979) have a DJ staff who have degrees from UT in Broadcasting and from the Professional Academy of Broadcasting, FCC Radio licenses, years and years of experience working at several area radio stations, and have played at hundreds of successful wedding receptions, class reunions, corporate functions, and school dances! When we say professional, we mean it! No DJ Service has as much experience as Pro-Audio Mobile DJs!

We specialize in corporate and wedding entertainment from cocktail hour to the after-party, offering customizable packages for every style and budget. 4AGTC has been invited to represent some of Tennessees most popular venues and event planners as a Preferred Vendor. We are known nation-wide for taking care of business, while developing a friendly and relatable rapport with our clients. We believe that your entertainment should be a fun, worry-free addition to your day. We are devoted to throwing you a fabulous party that reflects your personal style and offer an unsurpassed level of customization with our VIP packages.

Welcome to Sword Sounds, your premiere source for event entertainment and professional DJ service in east Tennessee. Your choice in entertainment is the most important decision in planning that next event, and the one that will set the tone for the memories you will cherish for years to come. Imagine for a moment that this is your Wedding Day, the most cherished day of your life. Youre at your reception and its no ordinary party. This is a once in a lifetime celebration, an event that the two of you have dreamt about since you were kids. This one moment in time deserves the finest of everything that the two of you could hope for.

Love, Peace & Happiness Band are a highly engaging act with lots of audience participation, named "Best of the Best" in Motown-style live band entertainment! Featuring musicians of the highest standard, with several years of notable experience within the music industry, this group makes a formidable team, with their tight harmony and wide repertoire. They not only charm the audience with their good musicality but also with their creative, choreographed moves on stage. If you want quality entertainment, this group is a must-have. They keep their audiences satisfied and wanting for more.

Remixed DJs is a wedding entertainment business operating out of Clarksville, TN. Whether you are hosting a large wedding or intimate gathering, this professional service will be a welcome addition to your celebration. The company offers everything from diverse music selections to uplighting and photo booth rental to make your wedding a joyous and unforgettable occasion.

My name is Jeremiah. I am the owner of Wubwoofer DJing Entertainment and located in Upper East Tennessee. I specialize in making your party, wedding, or event memorable and stress free! I also provide Photo Booth Rental, Tent Rental, and Digital Guest Book. I am so excited to get to know you and meet you! Feel free to check out my open event dates! If you have any questions please do not hesitate to reach out!

As a harpist, vocalist, composer, conductor, and songwriter, Timbre Cierpke is pioneering new sounds in both classical and commercial music, drawing from both worlds to create a truly unique neo-classical romantic minimalism. Timbre has been commissioned to compose string quartets, acapella choral works, and full orchestral compositions, including a yearly commission by the Jackson Symphony in Jackson TN. Her works have been performed all over the world, and she has also toured Scandinavia performing her own compositions with a full orchestra.

Mike Dunbar is a singer-songwriter in Nashville. His music is equal parts Paul Simon and Rolling Stones, blending lyrical depth with a rock and roll attitude. A native of New England, he earns his living as a professional writer and performing musician. He has been awarded grants from the Mellon Foundation and the College of the Holy Cross to compose and record original songs. His work has been featured in the Boston Globe as well as on The River and New Hampshire Public Radios All Things Considered. His newest single, "Let's Stay In" was recorded remotely with some of Nashville's premier session musicians.

The beauty of strings playing together as one ~ Experience this elegance on your most special day! Available for weddings, receptions, parties, anniversaries, or holiday festivities,The Rivendell String Quartet is perfect for any occasion where a touch of elegance is desired! Dedicated to providing a unique ambiance for your special event: The Rivendell String Quartet.

Affinity Entertainment began with one goal in mind: to design and create a live experience unlike any other; one that connects people and creates community through music. Affinity is defined as a spontaneous or natural liking for something. It is the only word that came close to explaining our passion for live events, and how we knew others would relate if they simply had the chance to experience them. After 500+ concerts & private events with countless notable venues, artists, DJs and clients, Affinity has seen growth and change in several ways. However, one thing shall always remain: in everything we do, we do For The Love Of Music.

I help wedding couples host creatively fun celebrations. As a polished Master of Ceremonies and Certified Wedding Coordinator, I have the experience to help you have the most memorable weddings that you and your guests will be talking about for the rest of your lives. Your wedding should reflect your romantic tale as a couple. We will work together to incorporate those characteristics that make your Love Story uniquely yours. Get ready to sing at the top of your lungs and pack the dance floor, creating memories of a lifetime. Well design your wedding to be filled with fun, smiles, laughter, and moments youll treasure the rest of your lives.

Rated as One of the Top Wedding Bands in the Capital District. The Ryan Clark Band is Known for Creating a Magical and Fun Atmosphere at Every Wedding! Ryan and his band bring a high energy experience to every wedding; offering the right balance of sophistication and fun. Customize your wedding experience during each step of the night with various services offered for ceremony, cocktail hour, reception and more.

The Corwin Trio is a professional string ensemble based in Nashville, Tennessee. If you're looking for experienced, friendly musicians to play for your wedding, special event, or recording session, we'd love to hear from you! We have been performing together for seven years in the greater Nashville area. Each member of our group is classically trained and holds Masters degrees in music performance. We offer consultation about song selection and can also write custom music arrangements. Whether you are looking for timeless classical selections or a contemporary, nontraditional feel, we are comfortable performing a wide variety of music.

The nights entertainment can make or break the planning of a great event. Our goal at M.I.N.E. is simple--to bring the party of Nashville's Lower Broadway directly to you. Now, the nights entertainment is one less thing for you to worry about, with musicians practiced in the art of throwing a great party.

By now you may know Austin Ellis from NBC's The Voice, is a Singing Acoustic Guitarist and DJ by profession. He performs a wide variety of genres including Top 40, Soul and R&B, Classic Rock, and original music. Austin can be hired by clients like you for venues, private parties, corporate events, weddings, and festivals. You can also get Austin to provide background/ambient music for intimate occasions like ceremonies, anniversaries, and engagements!

You deserve a customized experience that makes you feel seen and heard, and this experience should be fun and stress-free. Our main focus is the two of you. We are a husband and wife here to make your BIG DAY as stress-free as possible, create a wonderful experience during your ceremony and reception, and best of all? Capture all your memories! We are your local Sevierville, TN DJ & Photographer! However, we do travel and have served North Carolina, South Carolina, Kentucky, Alabama, and Georgia, and many more states!

Dj 316 has been keeping dance floors full for over 15 years and continues to build on his already impressive award winning resume on a weekly basis. Born in memphis, tennessee his first love will always be hip hop but his musical library include genres of all types (edm, gospel, chh, house, top 40, reggaeton, latin, rock, etc). He grew up in the memphis club scene and was inspired by the many local dj's in the M-town. He started DJ-ing in college because he loved to hear mixes on the radio and in clubs. Fast forward many parties and many years later and he's still going strong.

When throwing a big bash, you want to have something for everyone in your audience. From timeless party classics to the hippest, hottest tracks on the airwaves, Radio Incorporated covers literally every requested musical genre. Corporate events, weddings, galas, casinos  Radio Incorporated can entertain almost any crowd. Oldies, Motown, 80's, Top 40, country  like their slogan says, it's truly Every Style On The Dial!

Grab your bell bottoms, climb aboard some platform shoes, and get ready to show off your best Saturday Night Fever moves. When Dr. Zarr's Amazing Funk Monster is playing, there's no way you can resist the dance floor! One of the most popular Memphis bands ever to hit the party scene, Dr. Zarr has entertained legions of funky partygoers throughout the South for over two decades. From disco infernos to 80's New Wave, these guys have created one of the most energetic, fun, and professional dance bands you'll ever see.

ABOUT G3 The freshest R&B showband on the scene! G3, under the direction of Garry Goin, features awesome male and female vocals, first-rate sound, and a vast array of songs you love from the 50's to today. Upon finishing his formal education, Garry began traveling with various bands to gain hands-on experience. He honed his chops playing in groups that played everything from Jimi Hendrix to Roy Clarke to Earth Wind & Fire, eventually settling in Ft. Lauderdale, where his band backed Sly Stone.

ABOUT MEMPHIS ALL-STARS The Memphis All-Stars are exactly that: an all-star band of Memphis' finest and most respected musicians. From R&B to soul to rock 'n roll to any music your ears can imagine, the Memphis All-Stars will keep you on the dance floor all night long! A long-time casino favorite, this band is also available for private parties, weddings, and festivals. Performing over 250 dates a year, the Memphis All-Stars are professional, reliable, and supremely talented. So book the Memphis All-Stars, get on the dance floor, and let them make you feel like an all-star!

Alhough they hail from the Home of the Blues, the River Bluff Clan is leading the way in Memphis' growing love of bluegrass, Americana, and alt-country. Music of the River Bluff Clan evolves from multiple roots forms and cultural influences. Their bluegrass interpretation draws from Celtic and Appalachian traditions, along with the blues of the Mississippi hill country and Delta. It is thoughtful, soulful, energetic, and fun music that includes acoustic guitar, banjo, mandolin, fiddle, bass and vocals.

One of Memphis's Premier DJs, Tommy spins the tunes from yesterday to today's top hits. Whether its a private event or a corporate fundraiser Tommy is the perfect act for any occasion. Ask about his state-of-the-art Emulator technology, a large touchscreen interface that allows your guests to see Tommy working his magic right in front of their eyes!

One of the longest-running bands in the area, the Memphis Yahoos have been entertaining the masses in the Mid-South since 1996. This tight, professional, talented act plays all over the Mid-South  clubs, casinos, private events, etc.  and commands a large, loyal following. Their eclectic mixture of Top 40, classic rock, Motown, blues, and even a little straight-up country always gets toes tapping and dance floors filled. For a professional, affordable, reliable band, look no further than the Memphis Yahoos.

The Soul Shockers are the perfect R&B party band for your wedding reception, corporate event, fundraiser, or private party! With a repertoire that spans Motown and Stax to funk and disco to recent dance hits, the Soul Shockers are the region's hottest party band. This amazing band, led by high-energy front man Jerry Braxton, delivers an unmatched party experience, singing the songs that make people dance all night long. The Soul Shockers are probably Memphis' most popular choice for wedding receptions, as they are experts at entertaining a crowd from age 8 to 80. If they can't get a crowd on its feet and make it beg for more, no one can!

Peabody Rocket is an 8- piece band consisting of male lead singer, female lead singer, sax, trumpet, guitar, bass, keys, and drums. Originating out of "Music City" Nashville, TN, Peabody Rocket brings the party to any event, including wedding receptions, festivals, private and corporate events, and many more. Some party bands specialize in specific genres or eras of music- but not Peabody Rocket.

Almost Famous is the quintessential high-energy, sophisticated, versatile party band from Memphis. Tailoring themselves to their clients' needs, Almost Famous has played everything from storybook weddings and corporate events to sold-out stadiums. With show-stopping live performances and a high-fashion look, this quartet is the best in its field. Known as one of the most flexible and pleasant bands to work with, Almost Famous has become a must-have for party planners and the high-society crowd.

Renowned for their long-running stand as the house band at Alfred's on world-famous Beale Street, Kevin and Bethany Paige will bring energy and talent to your event. With a band of Memphis's best musicians and a truckload of dance tunes, they will provide class, fun, and a guaranteed good time. Plus, they ain't hard to look at either! Kevin had two Top 20 hits on Chrysalis records in the late 80's. He has toured extensively, opening for Debbie Gibson and playing with superstars too numerous to list. Kevin has also written songs and produced CD's for artists like Avalon, Point of Grace, Aaron Carter, etc.

The 1-900 Band was twice the winner of "Best Local Band" in the Memphis Commercial Appeal's "Memphis Most" contest! With a song list that spans generations and appeals to everyone from 8 to 80, the 1-900 Band can play any occasion: wedding receptions, corporate events, you name it. Male and female lead singers, two keyboard players, saxophone, guitar, and drums  this tight band can handle almost any request and keep the dance floor packed all night.

The members of A-440 are all-star veterans of the music industry, individually performing with some of the biggest legends in music history, including James Brown, Al Green, Rufus Thomas, B.B. King, among others, and they are sure to bring that same showmanship and musical finesse to your event!

The common thread that connects Beale Street, B.B. King's Blues Club, and The King Beez: They represent the best of the best of soul, R&B, and world-famous Memphis music. Beale Street is a mecca for blues, and B.B. King's Blues Club is the street's premier nightclub. The King Beez, center stage at B.B. King's for over 20 years, breathe new life into the very soul of R&B, for they have captured the essence of the genre. For over 20 years, the King Beez have set the standard for R&B bands in Memphis and beyond. Elegant and tasteful when required, funky and booty-shakin' when needed  the King Beez are truly the best of the best.

A professional ensemble comprised of violins, viola, and cello, the members of the Beth Luscombe Strings are classically trained and have played beautiful music at hundreds of events and weddings. Their repertoire ranges from classical to popular, from Bach to Andrew Lloyd Weber, from Mozart to Elvis. The group's flexible nature allows it to move easily between different areas, fit into small spaces, and be audible in a wide variety of venues. Beth can create a wide range of ensembles  trios, quintets, a harp, flute, and cello  all very different sounds but just as enchanting.

Hip, classy, professional: DJ Mark Anderson has been one of the Mid-South's premier disc jockeys for over 30 years. With years of DJ experience at Memphis' hottest clubs  including recent runs at Alfred's, Club Ten, Senses, and Rain  Mark can keep any dance floor jammed. Since 2007, Mark has been the house DJ at the Peabody Hotel's renowned weekly summer Rooftop Parties.

Featuring some of Memphis' most legendary musicians, Elmo & the Shades will turn any event into a rollicking, classic, rhythm-and-blues party! Lead singer Elmo Lee Thomas, the big man with the big voice, will take you on a musical tour of the best blues, R&B, and funk favorites of the last 50 years. Elmo's renowned bandmates include guys who have played on Stax, Hi, and Sun recordings and have performed in bands with James Brown, Isaac Hayes, Little Richard, The Bar-Kays, George Clinton, Otis Redding, Al Green, and many, many more. As the Memphis Flyer wrote, "This band has a musical pedigree that will blow your mind."

Big band swing with a huge horn sound! With up to 16 musicians, the New Memphis Hepcats can re-create the big band era with style, energy, and class. With standards from Duke Ellington, Benny Goodman, Frank Sinatra, and Count Basie to the ground-breaking tunes of Stan Kenton and Dizzy Gillespie, the band plays classic swing for all ages. The New Memphis Hepcats perform primarily at weddings, parties, and corporate events throughout the Mid-South. Re-create that glamorous era by booking the New Memphis Hepcats for your next function.

Jeremy is known to play 3 instruments simultaneously while singing. Now entertaining in the greater Memphis area and performing regularly at Graceland, Jeremy is a veteran of the 90s Seattle music heyday, as well as the Nashville studio recording scene. He has appeared on recordings and stages with the likes of Alan Jackson, Phil Vassar, The Judds, Vince Gill & Grant, and band members of such artists as Kenny Rogers, Razzy Bailey and the Allman Brothers. As an instructor with Blues In The Schools, he worked with founding Steve Miller Band guitarist Curley Cooke, teaching new life skills to juvenile felons at Echo Glen Children's Facility.

One of the most respected and talented mass choirs in the country, the Tennessee Mass Choir performs at high-profile events throughout the Mid-South and across the country. They brought the house down in Las Vegas for an international convention, and they got a standing ovation recently at a Memphis Chamber event at The Peabody Hotel. FedEx, Tupperware, Hilton Worldwide, and numerous galas, festivals, and special events have experienced the amazing musical power of this soul-stirring group.

Based in Nashville, TN, The Music City Sound is a 10-piece wedding band that performs at special occasions and private events. They deliver high-energy shows that cover a range of musical genres and will strive to have your loved ones on their feet from start to finish. The Music City Sound offers a one-stop-shop for all your wedding entertainment needs. You can choose between a six-piece or 10-piece set up for your celebrations to suit your venue. Their song lists include everything from ambient jazz to rock tunes and pop hits, so there is something for everyone on your big day.

Diamond Entertainment can offer a variety of services that will elevate your wedding. Whatever your music tastes, they will get the party going with all your favorites. They can offer not only star-quality DJ services but also violin services. On top of this, the team can offer lighting, sound/PA systems for your ceremony, cocktail hour, and reception

Picture this: as your guests take their seats, they hear the enchanting sound of a violin filling the air, creating a romantic and magical atmosphere that sets the perfect tone for your special day. Ansar Violin is the perfect violinist to add a touch of elegance and sophistication to your wedding ceremony, cocktail hour, or reception. Ansars versatility and talent allow him to play a wide variety of music genres, adding a unique touch to your ceremony or reception. You can walk down the aisle to your favorite song or have your guests serenaded to beautiful violin renditions of a modern hits during cocktail hour.
